The National Student Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS) will release funding decisions for all applicants for the 2020 academic year from January 6. Spokesperson Kagisho Mamabolo says funding decisions will be communicated to applicants via the MyNSFAS portal. “We are busy processing all applications that we have received. Funding decisions will be communicated effective the 6th of January 2020 and all funding decisions will be communicated to applicants via the NSFAS portal… therefore we encourage all applicants to check their applications online.  You can still use the same login details to see which stage your application has gone through up to date.” All applicants are advised to check the status updates online to track the application progress, while awaiting for final outcome. 